<section>
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;samp&gt;</code> element represents sample output from a computer program. VB styles it in <code>var(--font-mono)</code> at <code>0.9em</code>. It is part of VB's code-family elements alongside <a href="/docs/elements/native/code/"><code>&lt;code&gt;</code></a>, <a href="/docs/elements/native/kbd/"><code>&lt;kbd&gt;</code></a>, and <code>&lt;var&gt;</code>, and is automatically protected from machine translation via the <a href="/docs/i18n/">i18n system</a>.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>When to Use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Command output:</strong> Results from terminal commands</li>
      <li><strong>Error messages:</strong> System error text</li>
      <li><strong>Status messages:</strong> Build output, test results</li>
      <li><strong>API responses:</strong> Showing what a system returns</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>When NOT to Use</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>For code the user writes &mdash; use <a href="/docs/elements/native/code/"><code>&lt;code&gt;</code></a></li>
      <li>For keyboard input &mdash; use <a href="/docs/elements/native/kbd/"><code>&lt;kbd&gt;</code></a></li>
      <li>For variables &mdash; use <code>&lt;var&gt;</code></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Examples</h2>

    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/samp-examples.html" url="samp-examples.html" title="Sample output" shadow></browser-window>

