    <h3>Mixed with kbd</h3>
    <p>Pair <code>&lt;kbd&gt;</code> (user input) with <code>&lt;samp&gt;</code> (system response) to document command-line workflows:</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Input + output">{{ mixedCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>CSS Reference</h2>
    <code-block language="css" show-lines label="samp CSS">{{ sampCssCode | escape }}</code-block>
    <p>Unlike <code>&lt;code&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;samp&gt;</code> has no background or padding &mdash; output text should feel like raw system text, not highlighted code.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Screen readers read <code>&lt;samp&gt;</code> as regular text &mdash; the monospace styling is visual only</li>
      <li>Provide context: "The system responded with..." or "Error:" before the output</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

